In this article, President Trump makes remarks in the Cabinet Room regarding various topics. He praises Rick Perry for his work on energy and announces that Perry's recommended successor will be outstanding. Trump thanks Mexico for their assistance in reducing border numbers and mentions the loopholes that could be easily changed if Democrats took action. He discusses the strong economy and employment rates, particularly for African American, Asian American, Hispanic American, and women. Trump highlights the success of the stock market and the trade deals signed with Japan and South Korea. He criticizes Nancy Pelosi for not signing the USMCA trade deal and accuses her of using it to gain support for impeachment. Trump also addresses rumors of a heart attack and expresses his frustration with the media. He concludes by discussing the credibility of Lieutenant Colonel Vindman and the ongoing trade negotiations with China.